Incurrent siphonal opening located almost ventrally, at least twice as wide as excurrent siphonal opening. Excurrent siphonal opening located posteriorly; angle formed by junction of margins of two valves in posterior direction subtending excurrent siphonal opening (
Figures 30, 33
).

